Former Toronto Mayor Rob Ford has announced that he will undergo ` very serious ' surgery to remove a cancerous tumor in his abdomen .
In an emotional press conference on Thursday , the 45-year-old politician said he met with doctors who told him chemotherapy and radiation have shrunk the tumor to a size where they can operate .
Four surgeons will carry out the eight - to ten-hour operation on May 11 , and he will remain in hospital for 10 to 14 days .
